ICMA Sept 18 2024

?ChickWeight
ChickWeight %>%
  select(weight)
ChickWeight %>%
  head(3)
chick_clean <- ChickWeight %>%
  select(chick_id = Chick,
         diet = Diet,
         age_days = Time,
         weight_gm = weight)
chick_clean %>%
  arrange(chick_id)
chick_clean %>%
  mutate(session = case_when(TRUE         ~ as.character(age_days),
                             age_days == 0 ~ "birth",
                             age_days == 20 ~ "last1",
                             age_days == 21 ~ "last2"
                             ))
chick_clean %>%
  mutate(weight_lbs = weight_gm/453.6) 
chick_clean %>%
  mutate(weight_lbs = weight_gm/453.6) %>%
  group_by(diet, age_days) %>%
  summarise(N = n(),
            mean_wgt_gm = mean(weight_gm),
            mean_wgt_lbs = mean(weight_lbs)) %>%
  arrange(-age_days) %>%
  filter(age_days == 20)
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'diet'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
chick_clean %>%
  filter(age_days == 20) %>%
  mutate(weight_lbs = weight_gm/453.6) %>%
  group_by(diet) %>%
  summarise(N = n(),
            mean_wgt_gm = mean(weight_gm),
            mean_wgt_lbs = mean(weight_lbs))

ChickWeight %>%
  ggplot(aes(y = weight, x = Time, color = Diet)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth()
`geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'


ChickWeight %>%
  ggplot(aes(y = weight, x = Time, color = Diet)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .5) + #Transparency
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE)+ #best fits and removes confidence interval
  theme_minimal() +
  facet_grid(~Diet)+ #Splitting up into individual graphs by diet
  labs(y = "weight in grams", x = "time in days", title = "Chick Weight Over Time With Varying Diets") #Changing Axis Labels

ICMA Oct 28 2024

Communicating data

Jargon: Dont use jargon that is not explained, try to stick to very well known acronyms like AI, or explain only what is necessary

Tell a story: Use analogies and metaphors

The power if three: Things are easuer to remember in 3s

Inroduction: Should have a big question or problem statemement. Literature review to motivate the problem statement Little quesion should be related to big questino but more small and manageable

Tell me what your gonna tell me, then tell me, then tell me again what you just told me

Zotero
